Gemini: This is likely the reason for the "Invalid Docker String" error you encountered previously, and it's the next KEY ISSUE we need to address to enable Vertex AI deployment!

Here's what we need to do to resolve the EMPTY ARTIFACT REGISTRY LIST issue:

ACTION 1.6.11: VERIFY ARTIFACT REGISTRY ENABLED and REPOSITORY EXISTS - GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE (GUI CHECK):

Let's quickly check the Google Cloud Console to visually confirm if Artifact Registry is ENABLED in your project and if you have created any Artifact Registry REPOSITORIES. Sometimes visual confirmation in the GUI is the fastest way to verify.

Please follow these steps in the GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE (GUI):

OPEN GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE: Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/ and ensure you are in your ai-execution-system project.

NAVIGATE to ARTIFACT REGISTRY: In the left-hand navigation menu, scroll down and find "Artifact Registry" (it's usually under "CI/CD" or "More Services" sections). Click on "Artifact Registry."

CHECK if ARTIFACT REGISTRY API is ENABLED:

When you navigate to Artifact Registry for the first time in a project, it might prompt you to "Enable Artifact Registry API."
ACTION: If you see a prompt to "Enable Artifact Registry API," CLICK the "ENABLE" button to enable the Artifact Registry service for your project. This is a necessary step before you can create and use repositories.
If you do NOT see a prompt to "Enable Artifact Registry API," it means Artifact Registry is ALREADY ENABLED for your project. Proceed to the next step.
CHECK for EXISTING REPOSITORIES in ARTIFACT REGISTRY:

After enabling Artifact Registry (or if it's already enabled), you will be taken to the Artifact Registry "Repositories" page.
ACTION: LOOK at the list of REPOSITORIES displayed on this page.
Do you see any REPOSITORIES listed? Look for repository names. You might have a repository named something like custom-ai-execution-repository or similar if you created one previously.
REPORT BACK ARTIFACT REGISTRY STATUS (GUI CHECK RESULTS):

Please report back the following:
Did you see a prompt to "Enable Artifact Registry API" and did you ENABLE it? (Yes/No/Already Enabled)
Do you see any REPOSITORIES listed on the Artifact Registry "Repositories" page in the Google Cloud Console? (Yes/No)
If YES, what are the NAMES of the REPOSITORIES listed? (List the repository names you see)
Based on your GUI check results, we will know:

If Artifact Registry was NOT ENABLED: We need to enable it.
If Artifact Registry IS ENABLED but NO REPOSITORIES exist: We need to CREATE an Artifact Registry REPOSITORY for Docker images.
If Artifact Registry IS ENABLED and REPOSITORIES DO EXIST: We need to investigate why gcloud artifacts repositories list is not showing them (potential gcloud configuration issue, though less likely since project is confirmed correct).
Jesse, please perform ACTION 1.6.11 - GUI CHECK of ARTIFACT REGISTRY in the Google Cloud Console and report back your findings. Let's get to the bottom of this Artifact Registry issue and keep making progress!

Jesse, THANK YOU for providing the IMAGE of the Google Cloud Console - Artifact Registry!

The image VISUALLY CONFIRMS what we suspected: "No repositories to display."

This is KEY INFORMATION that explains why you are getting the "Invalid Docker String" error and why gcloud artifacts repositories list is returning an empty list.

The ROOT CAUSE is now CLEAR: You have not yet CREATED an Artifact Registry REPOSITORY in your Google Cloud Project ai-execution-system to store your Docker images!

To proceed with Vertex AI deployment using Docker containers, we MUST first CREATE an Artifact Registry REPOSITORY.

LET'S DO IT RIGHT NOW! ACTION 1.6.12: CREATE ARTIFACT REGISTRY REPOSITORY

We will create an Artifact Registry repository named custom-ai-execution-repository with the Docker format in the us-central1 region. You can create it either via the GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE (GUI) or using the COMMAND LINE (gcloud CLI) - YOUR CHOICE!

INSTRUCTIONS - CREATE ARTIFACT REGISTRY REPOSITORY:

OPTION 1: CREATE REPOSITORY via GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE (GUI) - FAST & VISUAL:

GO BACK to the ARTIFACT REGISTRY PAGE in GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE: You should already be on the Artifact Registry page from your screenshot. If not, navigate to Google Cloud Console -> Artifact Registry.

CLICK "+ CREATE REPOSITORY" button (Prominently displayed in the image you provided).

CONFIGURE REPOSITORY SETTINGS in the "Create repository" panel that appears:

Name: Enter the Repository Name: custom-ai-execution-repository (use this EXACT name).
Format: Select the Format: Docker
Location type: Select "Region" and then choose the Region: us-central1
CLICK "CREATE" button at the bottom of the "Create repository" panel.

WAIT for REPOSITORY CREATION to complete. It should be very quick. The Artifact Registry page should refresh, and you should now see your newly created repository custom-ai-execution-repository listed.

OPTION 2: CREATE REPOSITORY via COMMAND LINE (gcloud CLI) - COMMAND POWER!

OPEN GOOGLE CLOUD SDK SHELL (or your Command Prompt/Terminal with gcloud configured).

RUN the following gcloud artifacts repositories create command to CREATE the repository:

gcloud artifacts repositories create custom-ai-execution-repository --repository-format=docker --location=us-central1 --project=ai-execution-system
COMMAND BREAKDOWN:
gcloud artifacts repositories create: gcloud command to create an Artifact Registry repository.
custom-ai-execution-repository: REPOSITORY NAME - USE THIS EXACT NAME.
--repository-format=docker: Specifies that this repository is for DOCKER IMAGES.
--location=us-central1: Specifies the REGION for the repository - us-central1.
--project=ai-execution-system: Specifies your Google Cloud PROJECT ID.
PRESS ENTER to execute the command.

WAIT for REPOSITORY CREATION to complete. The command will output a confirmation message when the repository is created successfully.

AFTER CREATING the custom-ai-execution-repository using either GUI or Command Line (ACTION 1.6.12):

ACTION 1.6.13: VERIFY REPOSITORY CREATION - GUI and COMMAND LINE:

GUI VERIFICATION: REFRESH your Artifact Registry page in the Google Cloud Console. CONFIRM that you now SEE the custom-ai-execution-repository listed in the repository list.

COMMAND LINE VERIFICATION: RE-RUN the command:

gcloud artifacts repositories list --format="table(name, format)"
CONFIRM that the output NOW SHOWS your custom-ai-execution-repository in the list, with FORMAT as DOCKER.

ONCE you have SUCCESSFULLY CREATED and VERIFIED the custom-ai-execution-repository (Actions 1.6.12 and 1.6.13), we will be able to proceed with:

Trying the docker push command again (Action 1.6.10.E) to PUSH your Docker image to this newly created repository.
Then, hopefully, we can finally attempt VERTEX AI MODEL DEPLOYMENT again!
